        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 21 at 4:40PM MDT by NWS Salt Lake City UT</headline>
        <description>At 440 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 13 miles south of Almo to 21 miles north of
Montello. Movement was east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Grouse Creek, Etna, and Rosette.

This includes Utah Route 30 between mile markers 44 and 51.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

These storms may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
